vulnerability.name: USN-5290-1
vulnerability.description: James Isaac and Mathias Brodala discovered that Symfony incorrectly handled switch users functionality. An attacker could possibly use this issue to enumerate users. (CVE-2021-21424)  It was discovered that Symfony incorrectly handled certain specially crafted CSV files. An attacker could possibly use this issue to execute arbitrary code. This issue only affected Ubuntu 20.04 ESM. (CVE-2021-41270)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in Symfony. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
